Date: Fri 22 Dec 2017 14:22
Source: Get Surrey [edited]
http://www.getsurrey.co.uk/news/uk-world-news/sainsburys-recalls-beefburgers-after-people-14073028


Customers who have purchased packs of Taste the Difference beef burgers from Sainsbury's are being told to avoid eating them after people "became unwell with _E. coli_". The retailer is recalling its 4-pack Aberdeen Angus British Beef Quarter Pounders.

The Food Standards Agency said a very small number of people had caught _E. coli_ O157, which can cause vomiting, fever, diarrhea and abdominal pain. Symptoms can last up to 14 days and while most people get better without treatment, it can lead to serious complications and kidney failure.

Anyone who bought packs of these burgers, which have best before dates in July, September or October 2018, should return them.

[Byline: Nathan Hyde]

